ne-height: 170%;text-align: left;"><img src=3D"https://gallery.mailchimp.c=
om/13eb080d8a315477042e0d5b1/images/2e292385-dc1c-4cfe-b95e-845f6f98c2ec.p=
ng" align=3D"left" style=3D"-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic;border: 0;heig=
ht: auto;line-height: 100%;outline: none;text-decoration: none;padding: 5p=
x 30px 10px 0px;display: inline;width: 50px!important;">A thinker (like [=
Ralph Waldo Emerson]) misleads us as soon as he promotes harmony as the ex=
clusive goal=2C and especially misleads us when he preaches harmony as a <=
em>method</em>. Man=E2=80=99s life is full of contradiction and he <em>mus=
t</em> be; we see through a glass darkly =E2=80=94 we want more than we ca=
n have; we see more than we can understand. But a contradiction that is <e=
m>faced</em> leads to true knowledge=E2=80=A6 Contradictions are on the su=
rface=2C the symbols of deeper and more fertile forces that can unleash th=
e most marvelous energy when they are embraced. Never try to achieve =E2=
=80=9Corder=2C=E2=80=9D sacrifice symmetry =E2=80=94 seek to relate all th=
ese antagonistic forces=2C not to let the elimination of one to the other.=
