tration perhaps most widely relevant beyond poetry is that of narrative=
 =E2=80=94 our supreme hedge against the entropy of existence. Hirshfield=
 writes:</p><blockquote style=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-text-s=
ize-adjust: 100%;display: block;-webkit-margin-before: 0;-webkit-margin-af=
ter: 0;-webkit-margin-start: 40px;-webkit-margin-end: 0px;"><p style=3D"-w=
ebkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #808080;fon=
t-family: Arial=2C Sans-serif;font-size: 14px;line-height: 170%;text-align=
: left;"><img src=3D"https://gallery.mailchimp.com/13eb080d8a315477042e0d5=
b1/images/2e292385-dc1c-4cfe-b95e-845f6f98c2ec.png" align=3D"left" style=
=3D"-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic;border: 0;height: auto;line-height: 10=
0%;outline: none;text-decoration: none;padding: 5px 30px 10px 0px;display:=
 inline;width: 50px!important;">Storytelling=2C like rhetoric=2C pulls us=
 in through the cognitive mind as much as through the emotions. It answers=
 both our curiosity and our longing for shapely forms: our profound desire=
 to know what happens=2C and our persistent hope that what happens will so=
mehow make sense. Narrative instructs us in both these hungers and their s=
atisfaction=2C teaching us to perceive and to relish the arc of moments an=
d the arc of lives. If shapeliness is an illusion=2C it is one we require=
 =E2=80=94 it shields against arbitrariness and against chaos=E2=80=99s co=
mpanion=2C despair. And story=2C like all the forms of concentration=2C co=
nnects. It brings us to a deepened coherence with the world of others and=
 also within the manny levels of the self.</p><p style=3D"-webkit-text-siz=
e-adjust: 100%;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #808080;font-family: Aria=
l=2C Sans-serif;font-size: 14px;line-height: 170%;text-align: left;">[=E2=
=80=A6]</p><p style=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-text-size-adjust=
: 100%;color: #808080;font-family: Arial=2C Sans-serif;font-size: 14px;lin=
e-height: 170%;text-align: left;">Story remains a basic human path toward=
 the discovery and ordering of meaning and beauty.</p></blockquote><img sr=
c=3D"https://i0.wp.com/www.brainpickings.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/th=
ejacket9.jpg" style=3D"-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic;border: 0;height: a=
uto;line-height: 100%;outline: none;text-decoration: none;display: inline;=
width: 400px;"><p class=3D"caption" style=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100=
%;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #808080;font-family: Arial=2C Sans-ser=
if;font-size: 12px;line-height: 145%;text-align: left;border-bottom: 1px s=
olid #bfbfbf;padding: 0 0 4px;font-weight: bold;-webkit-margin-before: .35=
em;">Illustration by Dasha Tolstikova from <a href=3D"http://brainpickings=
=2Eus2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=3D13eb080d8a315477042e0d5b1&id=3Dd06da0=
68ba&e=3Da5eb5cdf67" style=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-text-siz=
e-adjust: 100%;color: #C33737;text-decoration: underline;"><em>The Jacket<=
/em></a> by Kirsten Hall=2C a sweet illustrated story about how we fall in=
 love with books</p><p style=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-text-si=
ze-adjust: 100%;color: #262626;font-family: Georgia=2C serif;font-size: 15=
px;line-height: 175%;text-align: left;">Echoing Ursula K. Le Guin=E2=80=99=
s abiding wisdom on <a href=3D"http://brainpickings.us2.list-manage1.com/t=
rack/click?u=3D13eb080d8a315477042e0d5b1&id=3D62c7de8db2&e=3Da5eb5cdf67"=
 style=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;color:=
 #C33737;text-decoration: underline;">how imaginative storytelling expands=
 our repertoire of possibilities</a>=2C Hirshfield adds:</p><blockquote st=
yle=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;display:=
 block;-webkit-margin-before: 0;-webkit-margin-after: 0;-webkit-margin-sta=
rt: 40px;-webkit-margin-end: 0px;"><p style=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 1=
00%;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #808080;font-family: Arial=2C Sans-s=
erif;font-size: 14px;line-height: 170%;text-align: left;"><img src=3D"http=
s://gallery.mailchimp.com/13eb080d8a315477042e0d5b1/images/2e292385-dc1c-4=
cfe-b95e-845f6f98c2ec.png" align=3D"left" style=3D"-ms-interpolation-mode:=
 bicubic;border: 0;height: auto;line-height: 100%;outline: none;text-decor=
ation: none;padding: 5px 30px 10px 0px;display: inline;width: 50px!importa=
nt;">Story=2C at its best=2C becomes a canvas to which the reader as well=
 as the writer must bring the full range of memory=2C intellect=2C and ima=
ginative response. The best stories are almost mythlike in their ability t=
o support alternative readings=2C different conclusions.</p><p style=3D"-w=
ebkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #808080;fon=
t-family: Arial=2C Sans-serif;font-size: 14px;line-height: 170%;text-align=
: left;">[=E2=80=A6]</p><p style=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-te=
xt-size-adjust: 100%;color: #808080;font-family: Arial=2C Sans-serif;font-=
size: 14px;line-height: 170%;text-align: left;">Narrative carries the know=
ledge of our alteration through the shifting currents of circumstance and=
 time.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-text=
-size-adjust: 100%;color: #262626;font-family: Georgia=2C serif;font-size:=
 15px;line-height: 175%;text-align: left;">Narrative=E2=80=99s essential c=
ounterpart is voice =E2=80=94 the waveform of the soul in writing. Hirshfi=
eld writes:</p><blockquote style=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-tex=
t-size-adjust: 100%;display: block;-webkit-margin-before: 0;-webkit-margin=
-after: 0;-webkit-margin-start: 40px;-webkit-margin-end: 0px;"><p style=3D=
"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #808080;=
font-family: Arial=2C Sans-serif;font-size: 14px;line-height: 170%;text-al=
ign: left;"><img src=3D"https://gallery.mailchimp.com/13eb080d8a315477042e=
0d5b1/images/2e292385-dc1c-4cfe-b95e-845f6f98c2ec.png" align=3D"left" styl=
e=3D"-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic;border: 0;height: auto;line-height: 1=
00%;outline: none;text-decoration: none;padding: 5px 30px 10px 0px;display=
: inline;width: 50px!important;">A person=E2=80=99s heard voice is replete=
 with information. So it is with the voice of a poem.</p><p style=3D"-webk=
it-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #808080;font-f=
amily: Arial=2C Sans-serif;font-size: 14px;line-height: 170%;text-align: l=
eft;">[=E2=80=A6]</p><p style=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-text-=
size-adjust: 100%;color: #808080;font-family: Arial=2C Sans-serif;font-siz=
e: 14px;line-height: 170%;text-align: left;">Voice =E2=80=A6 is the body l=
anguage of a poem =E2=80=94 the part that cannot help but reveal what it i=
s. Everything that has gone into making us who we are is held there. Yet w=
e also speak of writers =E2=80=9Cfinding their voice.=E2=80=9D The phrase=
 is both meaningful and odd=2C a perennial puzzle: how can we =E2=80=9Cfin=
d=E2=80=9D what we already use? The answer lies=2C paradoxically=2C in the=
 quality of listening that accompanies self-aware speech: singers=2C to st=
ay in tune=2C must hear not only the orchestral music they sing with=2C bu=
t also themselves. Similarly=2C writers who have =E2=80=9Cfound a voice=E2=
=80=9D are those whose ears turn at once inward and outward=2C both toward=
 their own nature=2C thought patterns=2C and rhythms=2C and toward those o=
f the culture at large.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"-webkit-text-size-adju=
st: 100%;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #262626;font-family: Georgia=2C=
 serif;font-size: 15px;line-height: 175%;text-align: left;">In the essay=
=E2=80=99s closing passages=2C Hirshfield once again captures a central tr=
uth about poetry that sets free a larger truth about life itself =E2=80=94=
 about the limits of attention=2C about the relationship between what is k=
nown and what is knowable=2C about the nature of transformation=2C about t=
he perennial incompleteness of being. She writes:</p><blockquote style=3D"=
-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;display: block;-=
webkit-margin-before: 0;-webkit-margin-after: 0;-webkit-margin-start: 40px=
;-webkit-margin-end: 0px;"><p style=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-=
text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #808080;font-family: Arial=2C Sans-serif;fon=
t-size: 14px;line-height: 170%;text-align: left;"><img src=3D"https://gall=
ery.mailchimp.com/13eb080d8a315477042e0d5b1/images/2e292385-dc1c-4cfe-b95e=
-845f6f98c2ec.png" align=3D"left" style=3D"-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic=
;border: 0;height: auto;line-height: 100%;outline: none;text-decoration: n=
one;padding: 5px 30px 10px 0px;display: inline;width: 50px!important;">No=
 matter how carefully we read or how much attention we bring to bear=2C a=
 good poem can never be completely entered=2C completely known. If it is t=
he harvest of true concentration=2C it will know more than can be said in=
 any other way. And because it thinks by music and image=2C by story and p=
assion and voice=2C poetry can do what other forms of thinking cannot: app=
roximate the actual flavor of life=2C in which subjective and objective be=
come one=2C in which conceptual mind and the inexpressible presence of thi=
ngs become one.</p><p style=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-text-siz=
e-adjust: 100%;color: #808080;font-family: Arial=2C Sans-serif;font-size:=
 14px;line-height: 170%;text-align: left;">Letting this wideness of being=
 into ourselves=2C as readers or as writers=2C while staying close to the=
 words themselves=2C we being to find in poems a way of entering both lang=
uage and being on their own terms. Poetry leads us into the self=2C but al=
so away from it. Transparency is both capacious and focused. Free to turn=
 inward and outward=2C free to remain still and wondering amid the mysteri=
es of mind and world=2C we arrive=2C for a moment=2C at a kind of fullness=
 that overspills into everything. One breath taken completely; one poem=2C=
 fully written=2C fully read =E2=80=94 in such a moment=2C anything can ha=
ppen. The pressed oil of words can blaze up into music=2C into image=2C in=
to the heart and mind=E2=80=99s knowledge. The lit and shadowed placed wit=
hin us can be warmed.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust=
: 100%;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #262626;font-family: Georgia=2C s=
erif;font-size: 15px;line-height: 175%;text-align: left;"><a href=3D"http:=
//brainpickings.us2.list-manage1.com/track/click?u=3D13eb080d8a315477042e0=
d5b1&id=3Dbbe5de3690&e=3Da5eb5cdf67" style=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 1=
00%;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #C33737;text-decoration: underline;"=
><strong><em>Nine Gates: Entering the Mind of Poetry</em></strong></a> is=
 a small but immensely largehearted book=2C replete with radiant wisdom on=
 the creative act of composing a life=2C in poetry or in pulse. Complement=
 it with Hirshfield=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"http://brainpickings.us2.list-man=
age.com/track/click?u=3D13eb080d8a315477042e0d5b1&id=3D01a4db4e85&e=3D=
a5eb5cdf67" style=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100=
%;color: #C33737;text-decoration: underline;">beautiful ode to the leap da=
y</a>=2C then revisit Mary Oliver on <a href=3D"http://brainpickings.us2.l=
ist-manage2.com/track/click?u=3D13eb080d8a315477042e0d5b1&id=3D2aeb387f36&=
e=3Da5eb5cdf67" style=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-text-size-adj=
ust: 100%;color: #C33737;text-decoration: underline;">what attention reall=
y means</a>=2C Elizabeth Alexander on <a href=3D"http://brainpickings.us2.=
list-manage2.com/track/click?u=3D13eb080d8a315477042e0d5b1&id=3Da85247a25c=
&e=3Da5eb5cdf67" style=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-text-size-ad=
just: 100%;color: #C33737;text-decoration: underline;">what poetry does fo=
